summary: This is an internal email chain from September 10, 2020, discussing budget constraints affecting the scanning and processing of Epstein-related materials from the Southern District of Florida (SDFL) and Office of Professional Responsibility (OPR). The sender notes they are out of money for the fiscal year and new work must wait.
keyFacts: Internal email from September 10, 2020 discusses budget constraints impacting Epstein case work.
Mentions need to hire a vendor to scan SDFL Epstein materials and help process OPR Epstein materials.
Work on Epstein-related documents may be delayed until October 2020 due to lack of funds.
Email indicates ongoing processing of Epstein materials by government offices as of late 2020.
